\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 When working on a long piece of writing, you may want to refer to research or other parts of the manuscript. In Scrivener, you can split the main editor into two and have different documents (or the same document) open in each.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Let\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s try that now by going to }{\f1\fs22\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>View > Editor Layout > Split Horizontally<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Alternatively, click on the button in the right of the editor header view (the square with the horizontal line through its middle):}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\qc\ltrch\loch {\*\shppict{\pict{\*\nisusfilename Clipboard Image}\picw211\pich107\picwgoal1500\pichgoal765\pngblip }}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u65532\'3F}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This document is now displayed in two panes.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Note:}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li763\fi-475\sa240\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::1>\tab \bullet \tab Through the }{\f1\fs22\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>View > Editor Layout<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  menu, you can switch to a vertical (side-by-side) split or remove the split to return to a single editor.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \bullet \tab Alt-clicking on the split button in the header view toggles between horizontal and vertical split mode.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \bullet \tab Clicking on the split button in the header view when there is a split removes the split, returning to single editor mode.<!$Scr_Ps::1>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Now let\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s load a }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 different}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  document in one of the editors:}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\i1 Select any document in the binder, and it will be shown in the editor that currently has the focus.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (You can tell which editor currently has the focus because when there is a split, the header bar of the focussed editor turns blue.)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You can also drag a document from the binder to the header view of the editor in which you wish to view it. Let\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s do that now:}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li763\fi-475\sa240\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::1>\tab 1.\tab Make sure that this document, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Splitting the Editor\u8221\'94, is visible in the bottom pane.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab 2.\tab Drag \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Sunset\u8221\'94 from inside the \u8220\'93Research\u8221\'94 folder onto the header view of the top pane.<!$Scr_Ps::1>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You can use the split view to view any two documents in Scrivener alongside one another, allowing you to refer to a text, PDF, image or media document in one editor while typing in another.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Try loading different documents into the other editor now. Remember, you can do this in two ways:}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li763\fi-475\sa240\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::1>\tab \bullet \tab Drag a document from the binder to the header view of the other editor.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \tab \bullet \tab Click into the editor you want to use so that its header turns blue, and then select a document in the binder.<!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::2>}
\par\pard\plain \tqr\tx10498\li44\fi-43\ri-1829\sa240\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs22\b1\i1\cf3 <$Scr_Cs::3>Tip<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f5\fs26\b0\i0 : Double-clicking on the central divider will resize the two editors so that they are of equal height or width.\tab <!$Scr_Ps::2>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Before moving on, let\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s close the other editor. Do this by clicking on the square button next to the up/down arrows in the right of the header view above }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 this}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  editor. (Clicking this button when there is already a split tells Scrivener to get rid of the split and remove the }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 other}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  editor.)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Next, click on \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Editor View Modes\u8221\'94.}}